I have an outgoing personality, never liking to stay holed up at home. May it be as simple as going out for a movie, a vacation or just window shopping, the great outdoors fascinate me. My first love though is books. I am a voracious reader and simply love Literature and Philosophy. I write poetry, short stories, philosophical dissertations and lyrics. column1: I am a Sachin Telugu community (Brahmin) settled in Mauritius and we are the third generation here. Actually my grandparents came from India. Believes in honesty, loyalty, truthfulness, simplicity as well as spirituality. My idea of soul mate should not be money minded. She should respect family values, and should be a daughter to my parents rather than only a daughter in law and must be my best friend as well. Should be God-fearing person with a golden heart and immense humility and faithful all the way.,"My idea of soul mate should not be money minded. Rather than a typical wife, I am looking for a partner who would accept me as I am and be my friend. Should be God-fearing person with a golden heart and immense humility and faithful all the way.  Also be able to maintain family relation in any situation. Someone who believes and respects in family values and traditions. Someone why think by her heart rather than being a calculative person and always practical.

She should believes in commitment in relations and understand others. I am looking for someone who understands me and balances my nature and who can be my friend and partner, someone who I can talk freely
Being faithful and Stan by my life partner in whatever the situation is my priority, and also expect that in return she should be loyal to me.
She should have a sense of humor and a friendly nature.

column1:
I am very good in taking care of my belongings and willing for a sensible life partner who can understand me so as to care for my feelings. I am a person of love. Not much expectations required but i need presence of someone who can understand me and i can understand her to make this journey of life more easy and luxurious. For me, i am very easy going personality who love to be loved. Ii assure that you will be considered equally as to me you will be priority. 
Apart from that i love to play guitar whenever i get free and also sing Ghazals & listen Sufi when in bad mood sign rock and play on my Acoustic with a perfect bass when in good mood....
I assure to be a very good husband you ever dreamt off. You should understand my feelings & i will do as well. If you find any problem in life the only man standing behind you to support will be me. 
I am looking for a friend and a soul mate who has all fours- 
Beauty attraction (generates desire), emotional connection (generates affection), mental/intellectual interaction (creates interest )and spiritual blending (creates Love), along with all this chemistry and compatibility brings cooperation, understanding and a hand and shoulder in times of happiness and need/stress for both, honesty, romance, care and love can make a very good cocktail for happy and satisfied life.,"I am very confident in myself. What i want, i do my full efforts to have it. But if one day i think that this thing/person is of no use to me or that thing do anything against me then i am not against that person but though i am in favor of that person and give that person the same regard as gave before. i care for my near ones.
You must be:
1. family oriented.
2. Should understand what family and relations are and what they mean.
3. Should have the ability and faith to tell whats going in your mind.
4. Never hesitate to me to tell your feelings whether positive or negative.
5. You can be anyone and everything for me unless and untill i am the one for you.

6. Dont come to me in any sort of pressure if so then allow me to advice you in better way. ",,26 to 31,25 Apr 1978,21:14:00,India,Delhi,Average,Average,0 brothers ,Agarwal,,Delhi,"Delhi College of Engineering, Delhi University",Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,B.A. (Arts),"35 yrs, 5ft 8in,

column1:
I am working as a lecturer in an Government Inter College ( it is BVM Inter College, Bharawan, District - Hardoi ) near Lucknow. I put up in Lucknow. 

I have done M. A. in English from Allahabad University, M. A. in Ancient History from Kanpur University and then B Ed from Kanpur University. 

Well.... now comes the difficult part of describing about myself :)). Let me give it an honest try. 

I am a level headed, mature and understanding person. 
An avid reader, easygoing and 'fun to be with' sort of person. 

It took a bit longer for my marriage as being a guardian I had some responsibilities. I first wanted to get all of my brothers/sisters settled first. By God's grace everyone is now either well settled or on the way of.

Though did not want to become a Lecturer as a first preference, I can't complain :). Fate always plays its hand well. At the end I am happy with whatever I am.


We are Gautam Rajpoots. Our ancestral origins go back to Argal State in Fatehpur (U.P.).

In my family, I have my mother and we are 7 siblings. 

My father passed away 6 years ago. 

Am eldest of all among us siblings.

Next to me is a sister who is married to a businessman (In Chauhan Rajpoots) in Fatehpur. 

The brother next to that i. e 2nd no brother, is a software engineer and is working in Royal Bank Of Scotland, Gurgaon. He used to work earlier in J P Morgan Chase, Mumbai.

3rd no. brother is M.A. , B. Ed. He is a registered contractor. He stays at home with mom, takes care of our farming and carries out his construction (road, school etc ) contracts. 

4th one is has finished his B. Com. and is now preparing for MBA entrance exams in Delhi. 

The last brother is in final year of B. Tech. (Computer Science) from Jaypee University of Engg. and Tech. Guna, MP. 

Youngest of all is a sister who is studying and preparing for engineering exams.

Overall, a well educated family and I have the honor of playing the role of the angel guardian :),"Looking for an understanding, mature partner. She should either be a working lady or somebody who plans to work after marriage.

The reason why I am looking for a working partner is, though I am earning a fairly decent salary for an individual, it might not be sufficient for a family to be run :)) And I'd be needing my partner's support to plan out things togather.",,25 to 31,05 Oct 1978,,India,Allahabad,Average,Doesn't Matter,,Kshatriya,Kshatriya,,,Very Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MA (Arts),"35 yrs, 5ft 7in,

column1: I am a very straightforward, honest, reasonable and dependable person.  After MBA from XLRI-Jamshedpur I have rejoined my organization (a power sector PSU which I had joined immediately after my engineering studies), due to the very accelerated growth possibilities. Currently I serve as Executive engineer, aligned to become a DGM after my forthcoming promotion. Along with my job I am also serving (for the second time) as the General Secretary of the Uttaranchal Power Engineers Association. During my MBA studies, I had represented XLRI as a core member of the External Linkages Committee (which manages PR and media relations for XLRI) and the Alumni Committee. I have been a visiting student at Tulane University, New Orleans, USA and have interned in USA as a management consultant. Family and close friends are very important to me, as are values. I love nature and arts. I enjoy reading and listening to music. I love nature and outdoor activities like whitewater rafting, kayaking, trekking etc. I like to swim, play lawn tennis and take long walks. I like to go out with close friends. On the spiritual front, I do meditation and Reiki along with yoga.,"I would like my partner to be intelligent and attractive, someone I enjoy talking to and look forward to spending my life with.

We would like her to be well educated, though IAA?A?m not looking for any particular qualification. I will respect her career aspirations (though I do not specifically require that she work) and would also be supportive if she wants pursue creative, academic or artistic interests. I want it to be a friendly and synergistic relationship.
I would respect her personal choices such as spirituality, dietary preferences etc. We would do our best to make her feel at home.

column1:
I am sanchayan sen(Rohan is my pet name, Dak naam), born in kolkata and staying here in delhi ever since my graduation days. Mine is a very small family, father passed way in 2008 and staying with mother. I ama loner by heart and i seek pleasures in natural beauty of life. Simple things as gentle smile and caring heart simply bowls me over. I am searching for someone who can be a wonderful friend with me and with whom i can share excellent vibes. I like to travel a lot and would like my partner to join me in the course of rediscovering ourselves. I do not believe in expectations and hence i do not expect anythign but love and respect. I expect my parter to be loving by heart and humble by nature. All i want is a wonderful friend to spend my entire life with.

More than a wife , i am looking for  a companion with whom i can explore life as it is. I love to go out in the evenings and would expect my partner to share my interests with me, and in the same mould i would like to immerse myself in her interests and hobbies.

I would like her to enjoy life in her sphere, would love to share my passion of music , movies and travelling with her. Although i am not too good at domestic chores but i would definitely help her in setting up our abode. I would like to make equal contribution towards her efforts to make our dwelling place a little heaven on earth.
It might sound too fancy but then i always have been aa die hard optimist to the core. When i have spare time with me, i love to write poems and indulge in literary activity. I am fond of animals and though i dont possess any pet of my own, i am open to adopting a pet if my partner so desires.
Ours would be a nuclear family and i would like to take her out in the evening to either socialise or to spend quality time with each other. We all have the dream of finding our ideal match in this world, it might never materialise but that should not stop us from making conscious efforts towards finding a soulmate for ourselves.
This is the essence of my posting my profile here on this forum.,"I am an essentially a Hum Tum member and would prefer my partner to believe in the same concept. I need a good friend , a lifelong companion with whom i can indulge in the small beauties of this world.

Since music and travelling are my passion, would really appreciate if my partner can accompany me in these pursuits. I would like to make myself an intricate part of her world and would love to accompany her in her own quest for happiness and bliss.",,21 to 31,23 Sep 1978,07:27:00,India,Kolkata,Athletic,Doesn't Matter,,Brahmin - Bengali,,,,Very Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MCA/PGDCA,"35 yrs, 5ft 7in,

He's the eldest child, and has a sister who's happily married. Lives with parents at Dharwad, Karnataka.,"I'm looking for a bride who comes from a well-cultured family, and is willing to be a home-maker or work in my own company (as per her wish) or work from home/be an entrepreneur.
I would like her to understand and be supportive of the fact that apart from a younger sister who is already married, I am the only son to my parents.

,I come from a well-cultured, middle-class traditional family with modern outlook. I have been brought up in an open and engaging environment where I have had the opportunities to make my choices and take my own decisions in life, and be accountable for them.

I live with my parents at Dharwad in the house which they constructed when I was very young. Father was working as Field Officer with MMTC (Minerals & Metals Trading Corporation) - a Government of India Public Sector Undertaking, and has retired a few years back. Mother is a home-maker. I have a younger sister who is married to a software engineer, has two children and is living in Bangalore.

Since I started working, I have progressively grown up in stature and maturity, acquiring material wealth along the way (I bought my own car a couple of years back without taking any loan), and my upbringing has kept me grounded in spite of the successes I have had as an entrepreneur.

column1:
Success always comes to a person who believes to work with sincerity and honestly. 
My case too is not different from it. Being born and brought up in a middle class family, I respect the traditional ideologies of a customary Indian family.

Mahatma Gandhi has been a great source of inspiration to me, for his beliefs in the philosophy of simple living and high thinking. I am a very down to earth man but at the same time quite progressive in my way of thoughts. I like the idea of a nuclear family, not because it is fast becoming popular in the Indian society but because of the privacy and the personal space it offers; which I believe is a dire need in todaya??s fast paced world. 

Another habit which fascinates me most is meeting people, having discussions and sharing my knowledge and experiences with them. I believe that this trait is good for personal development, and I enjoy doing the same. It is always preferable to make friends having identical thoughts and ideologies. My friends consider me a true companion as I am always with them in their good or bad times.  

Apart from all this I like to play games and watch cricket when I get any leisure time.

I believe that being ambitious is quite imperative for an individual to achieve desired objectives.  My long term objective is to establish myself well in my chosen career path so that I can fulfill the needs of my family efficiently.    
 
God is almighty and everyone including me believes in the existence of the god and his divinity. This makes my belief in the institution of marriage even stronger. For me marriage as an everlasting relationship between two souls, mutual faith and understanding between husband and wife are very essential facets of a successful marriage. That is how I think I can be a good husband to my wife.,"Life is full of ups and downs and one should be prepared to handle such ups and down.  My search for a life partner would end at a person who is matured and responsible enough to tackle these ups and downs of life. Understanding my feelings and walking hand-in-hand with each other all through our lives is what should make us true companions of each other. We should be able to complement each other in every aspect of life, be it personal and professional. Sharing of thoughts, ideas, dreams, suggestions and guidance should be a daily practice between us.  That is how I think we can make our relationship stronger and stronger.
Respect for elders and valuing their participation and involvement is our lives would be some traits that are appreciated and also cherished from a girl who would be an integral part of my family.

As I mentioned that I idolize Mahatma Gandhi and hence his way of life and merits attach great importance to me. Simplicity and honesty is another name that you can give to my lifestyle and I look up to having same traits in my partner as well.
Being simple doesna??t mean that I detest the modern way of thoughts and ideas. I am very much a todaya??s man but yes my way of life is not as pompous as most men of today would have it.

I would like that my partner should be career-minded and also have a growth path thought for herself, as I want her to be progressive and ambitious in life. I deem that being ambitious makes quite an impact on a persona??s mindset and thoughts, which is very important to make your mark on this world.

All through my life I have kept myself away from smoking, drinking and even a non-vegetarian diet. As per my knowledge all these ill habits are harmful to health as well as environment, hence I have never drawn myself to it; and I would appreciate if my future partner can also keep herself away from such prejudicial habits.
I am sure God would have certainly made someone for me; he just wants me to find her. ",,,11 Aug 1978,05:55:00,India,Gwalior,Average,,,Sonar,,,,Fair ,,Self,Masters,"35 yrs, 5ft 7in,

Hello there,
Thanks for stopping by to view my profile.

(from the boy) 
Describing myself is not something i get to do that often, but i will try to do my best this time.
I have had the opportunity to grow up in various places and enjoy the best of the local culture. Most of my growing up years have been split between India & USA, giving me a good blend of both the East and the West. My hometown in India is New Delhi.

I am very organized, goal oriented and career focused person. My determination and drive to acheive my goals has made me a successful individual in my career. My educational background is in Computer Sciences - Networking & Telecommunications and am currently pursuing an MBA in International Business. I am settled in the United States, my status being a permanent resident (Green Card holder) and work as a Project Leader in one of the leading Healthcare Information Systems corporation in the world.



Hobbies : I am actively involved in sports, both playing and watching it. Other interests : I love Music, Eating out, travelling to different places, going out with my friends, movies are a few of the common things that i like to do often. I also do love pets. There is a lot more to me than the limited number of words that I can type here. If my overall profile interests you then please dont hesitate to contact me and chat with me sometime.

Who my ideal future partner would be ?
I prefer someone who has either shared both cultures like me, with a blend of both east and west, or someone who is willing to explore the possibility of having a future of living outside india.

I am at a phase of my life where i am ready to meet someone to share some good experiences, memories, and to spend the next phase of my life with someone whom, we can trust each other, help each other in our ups and downs, and enjoy the future.

I would prefer my partner to be Someone with goals respective to their careers is appreciated. A healthy balance of work and family/life is very important to me.

Someone with strong family values is important, respect for the partner, respect for both elders and younger members of family and friends.

My family is very important to me and they are very liberal. My parents have done a great job of raising 2 kids, and providing us with the best of care, culture, and family values. So I welcome profiles of different cultures and backgrounds as well.





Have a good day searching for the one you believe you want to be with. If we happen to come across each other, then I shall look forward to it.
Regards,
--------------------------------------------

A bit about my family and background (provided by my parents)
------------------------------------------



We are basically tamil nadu based telugu brahmins settled in delhi for more than 20 yrs . About us : i am holding a very senior position in a public sector undertaking (delhi)and my wife is a homemaker and our daughter (done her MCA ) is married and residing in Chicago (USA) .

column1:
I said to myself that the lady that I am looking for should have a fair chance to find me first or, otherwise, get to know about me!! 

So... here I am!!!

Ergo, here's who I am!!!!

------

I am a thinking person. I know my mind and am independent; frank; responsible; trusting; trustworthy; and fearless. 
I am firm on my principles, but never harsh in my interactions. I am always up to helping people, but cannot be pushed around. 
I focus my energies on bringing about openness and sincerity in any relationship. I value the genuine empathy, the caring and the sharing that emerge out of such earnestness. 
Traveling is my passion -numero uno. I relish going places; meeting people; and enjoying the sights, sounds, tastes and aromas of different cultures and ways-of-life. 
I take interest in almost all kinds of arts and artistic manifestations - films; paintings; sculptures; dramas; magic; dance forms; literature (both prose and poetry) - and diligently pursue these interests. 
I derive superlative relaxation from listening to music (any time); from singing (often); and from dancing (occasionally). 
I consider myself to be a gourmet and derive as much pleasure from cooking (nothing fancy though - just simple, home-cooked Marathi fare), as I do, from trying out different cuisines or culinary items. 
I am an indefatigable admirer of nature and take special interest in 'People Watching'. I get along well with people and have the tact and humour that make for a good conversation. 
Self-expression and a well-balanced life are the things I am ambitious about and have been in the pursuit of - with reasonable success - which I am determined to keep up. 
As a 'Development Practitioner', my work pertains to 'Public Policy' research and analysis and designing, management and assessment of developmental projects. 
I believe there can be no end to how much and how well one can grow in the right companionship, even as this companionship is mutually cultivated - based on love; meaning; regard; reciprocation; and inspiration.,"In her I'll look for: an awareness of her self; the courage of conviction; a multi-faceted persona; and the zeal to admire, share and live-up life in all its colours and shades.

column1: Few words about my son Thank you for stopping by and having a look at my profile. It's always hard to describe yourself, I am a bubbly and a sociable person, good sense of humour, mix with all ages. Hobbies I enjoy playing snooker and enjoy watching Hindi soaps as and when I get the time. 1. How they look (Appearance) This is something that does not really matter to me. Looks are not what matters, it is what is on the inside, how the person have been brought up within their family life. 2. Age difference (the number of years between ages) To me, age is just a number six to eight years is the most comfortable for me, but I will consider anyone I feel I have a real connection with. 3. Religion denomination This is NOT very important to me. I am not going to turn down someone just because they don't attend a mandir, but she has to be strong in her faith. Don't get me wrong I believe in god and when I get the time I attend the Temple Religion is not forced onto anyone it's our faith and how we believe in it. 4. Financial security (Rich, poor) Honestly I don't care. I have always wanted to start with absolutely nothing so we knew we love Each other for us, not for what we have Money shouldn't dictate the two peoples life, as you are marrying someone for who they are and not their wealth 5. Education level (High school, College, etc) My bride would have to be able to discuss odd topics on at least an intelligent level I would say this requirement would lead to at least High school. 6. Attitudes towards life (Views on politics, issues, family) I am not much on politics so that doesn't really make much of a difference to me. As long as her moral views are similar to mine. Of course I wanted somebody who wants a family, but I didn't have an ideal number of kids I was shooting for. It's a dream that needs to be fulfilled together There's more to me but as stated earlier it's difficult to describe yourself to find out more email me and please provide your contact details so I can contact you. Thank you,,,,01 Mar 1978,14:10:00,United Kingdom,Others,Slim,Doesn't Matter,,Brahmin,,,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,Undergraduate,"35 yrs, 5ft 5in,

I believe life is full of adventure, trill, fun, problems & contradictions but you have to maintain a balance. You can not get everything right but you can assess & search anything right from a wrong. No tensions just think; do it or leave it. You must be clear in your thought and everything can be contradicted or can be solved. Full happiness but a bit seriousness. There must be a bundle of hobbies and no boredom but no habit. There is no need to change life but you can change you. It is a matter of approach. Sometimes a negative approach will work. You must say 'LET IT BE'. Excess of everything is bad. But there bust be perfection in everything you do. Besides this, I enjoy going for long walks, journeys, and traveling, adventurous things or just like to try out, when i find something exciting. I tried skeying, balooning, paraglyding, river-rafting etc. I visited many places specially Jabalpur, Amarnath, Kedarnath, neelkanth etc. many times. My date of birth is 15.11.77. Whatever the circumstances a smile on whose face would mean a lot to me and vice versa :) .....this may sound like over-high expectations, but I feel that these qualities, together with mutual love, respect, commitment, honesty understanding and trust are important for an interesting &   happy marriage. Needless to say, honesty is a sine qua non of it! She will get the same response with me also. She must have a bit humour with a sought of forgiveness and forgetness of the silly things in life. She has to just look at me in the tense surroundings. Till we are right, no situation can make us puzzle. It is equally important to take it in a spirit of practicality, which doesn?t make us neglect our responsibilities and aims!!

I am looking for a normal person who is intelligent, stable and would like to embark with me on this journey called life. column1: Our son aged IS 35 years is a BBM graduate. He worked in BESCOM, FEDEX, AVC Infotech and SLK software at junior level. He got first class in 10th standard and was above average. Mild Schizophrenia struck him at the age of 18. Early diagnosis and medication ensured debility well under control. His elder brother is happily married and settled in Canada with his wife and a son. We are in a dilemma whether our son should marry at all. Unable to decide between the parental obligations and the guilt of cheating a girl who would be his wife, we pondered over the issue for 7-8 years. Some of our friends and relatives advised he be married as the debility is not serious in nature. After giving a considered thought, we are now looking for a suitable bride for him. Our son often expresses his desire to marry but we are holding him up. He is honest, innocent, law abiding and a gentleman who would not harm others. He does not smoke and is a teetotaler. He left the job in August 2011. He is uncomfortable working in the company of others. He has inferiority complex and is self conscious. He drives 2 wheelers, cars, does all his personal works including banking. He maintains good physical health, sees TV programs, is fond of English songs and movies. About ourselves: I am 66 years old and retired and my wife 56 years. We are in good health and have no health problems. Expectations from our would be daughter in-law: Our would be daughter in-law should not a divorcee and can be a widow without children. She could be of 30-40 years, be a Kannadiga. She should be educated, gentle, caring and understanding. She should be able to put up with a gentle and a non violent patient. She could be non vegetarian but not beef or pork eating one. Caste no bar. Future of their married life: If everything goes well, it could be a happily married life. We will ensure them a comfortable life but definitely not a luxurious one. column1: Hi.. ! Thanks for browsing my profile. ! Basically I think that writing all the blah blah here does not make sense till you actually interact or communicate with the person. But to let things roll.. am mentioning a brief picture about me. My name is Hrishikesh. I am a grad in Chemical Engg and a post grad in textile design from NIFT Delhi. Currently have just started to pursue my PhD in design from CEPT university. I am an entrpreneur by nature and am putting my efforts to establish an identity for my recently started design studio. The rest like hobbies, nature, etc are all very simple and basic that make a human being. I like to be a warm and casual person, enjoy being friends, having a good time with my family. embarking on trips. Moivies, photography and other fields related to design is my passion. In fact I enjoy them more as a sense of activity for engrossment than a moneymaking venture. I am a visual thinker and the, how, what, who, which, when, where, whom aspects of knowledge intrigue me. I do have my ambitions in life but would not loose my calm by being impatient. Religion to me is more of a faith in the Almighty and His creations, rather than a dictum to be followed. Though I follow many dictums which have a logic and a deep philosophy to back them. They do have a postive effect on the life that you live. About companionshiip in life, well I thiink that its your karma that takes you where you belong. I am a strong believer in exposure and experience in life. Values and perceptions in life are what matter the most. They build up the broad nderstanding. They open up your mind and persona and that helps companions share a mutual relationship, live like buddies in thick and thin making every moment wonderful as time just passes away. , Concern, care, trust, faith and love is how any relationship progresses and every stage triggers a step further experience than the former and surely a better one. Phew.. I woudl stll like to reiterate that it would be interesting to interact and find out as the talk progresses rather than develop a judgemental attitude from all this text. After all, we are all looking out for buddies for life. Till then n'joy,,,,08 Jul 1978,19:20:00,India,Ahmedabad,Heavy,,,Vaishnav,,,,Wheatish ,,Self,Other Post Graduation,"35 yrs, 6ft,

column1: Dedication towards anything is a very good nature. I have always appreciated this in people and I appreciate this in myself too. I am a very dedicated person and not only just to work but towards other things too. This thing help me in my professional as well as my in personal life too. Even if I do something that is very minute, I devote  my whole time and concentration towards it. I pray to god that I always possess this quality. I have my own business of Engineering Product. I have a factory. Before this, I did Diploma in AutoCAD Designing from Delhi. I have many friends and they are very important to me. Some of them are very close to me and I treat them like my family members. I am sure if anything happens to them. I will take care of them and I will never leave them alone. When I am free, I like to listen to music and watch movies. Whenever I get some days off from work or I have less workload I go out for holidays with friends or family.,"I want to be very specific about one thing. The woman I get married to should be a teacher. I prefer this because I like the way teachers are so responsible towards things. They are good at dealing things and they know how to take sensible decisions.

Another reason why I want to marry a teacher is because they are a little less occupied compared to any other profession. This way she can take care of her career and household together without getting stressed.

If she feels stressed, I will be there for her. I can help her out with anything thing she wants, it can be her job, family or household. I am not one of those men who feel disgraced like many other Indian men do.

I am traditional but dona??t mind being modern if it is convenient. I prefer what is practical. Therefore, she can be either be traditional or modern or a combination of both. I mind none and have no reservations about that.

I am very honest and I would expect the same quality in her. I also want her to respect my family and if she does, she will receive a lot of love from them. All she has to do is be herself as I dona??t appreciate artificiality.

We can make the most of what we get and enjoy our life to the fullest. Even if we dona??t have the best time, we can support each other and make it the best. all we need is love and support. ","My mother is a homemaker and my father is a business man like me. My brother expired. I have one sister now and she is happily married. I love my family and I feel they are my responsibility. column1: What do you say on a forum as impersonal as the internet esp. when you are seeking a soul mate ??... Well you put in what you think is your honest picture of yourself and hope (REALLY HARD) that there is someone out there who is looking for someone like you !!! So here goes, I am a simple but very liberal (in thought and action) muslim who believes that the religion you practise is incidental to your birth. Dont get me wrong, I am a proud muslim but someone who doesnt quite agree with the picture of the religion that is painted by many a zealot across the world and one who openly defies dogma. Whoops this turned out to be quite a controversial start to my personality. Anyway, I am a postgraduate who currently works in the FMCG sector and makes enough to ensure that he doesnt have to go hungry and undertake his other passions - Music and Traveling without having to think about what next? I love traveling, food, reading and music, not necessarily in the same order. I have few but very supportive friends who I know I can wake up in the middle of the night without hesitation and a fantastically awesome family that comprises my two younger brothers and my parents. These are people I can kill for and I know they would do the same for me. As for the rest, I have a lot of acquaintances as part of my job, but then who doesnt in today's world !!! I am looking for a companion, someone who I can hold a conversation with and not someone who necessarily matches with me on a "list of criteria met", cause I honestly dont know who that person and what she would be doing? I am looking for someone who likes whats closest to my heart - Music & traveling coz I would like to share these moments with that special someone (else either the girl would get mad at the constant music playing around in the house or will run away with a more stable stay at home typa guy as I am constantly "planning", if not actually on a holiday somewhere). All the rest of it would probably be incidental if we can cross these fundamental but monumental hurdles;-) Anyway wont make this into an autobiography so will let a few things be unsaid so that we have something to talk about incase someone does decide to get in touch !!! So here is hoping and crossing fingers :),,,25 to 29,28 Jun 1978,,India,Bangalore,Heavy,,,Sunni,Sunni,,,Wheatish ,,Self,MBA/PGDM,"35 yrs, 5ft 9in,

column1: Ronobijay is an excellent photographer, very keen reader, well-travelled, trained in western classical music and a good leader. He is an extrovert, who enjoys spending time with his friends and family - and is a responsible and excellent son. We believe he is a fine, sensitive and fun-loving human being - and is adored by all his friends and relatives. He is a keen quizzer and debate-enthusiast AA?A? having represented and won several championships for his school, college and company. He has won numerous awards through school, college and post-graduation - as well as recognized for his passion for excellence at work. He has won several management and leadership awards at his workplace over the last few years. He is an active participant in social causes as well. Education Background: Convent schooled B.E. (Electronics & Telecom) from a top-college in Pune University (PICT) MBA from Indian Institute of Technology, Madras He is currently working in a top MNC in Bangalore as an Analytics Manager - and leads the WW Sales Analytics function there. About us, the family: We are a very close-knit nuclear family, settled in Pune for over 35 years - and are reasonably well-known and regarded in the Bengali circle here. Ronobijay has a younger brother - Aribijay - a Computer Engineer working in a technology company- who is married to Pallavi. His mother, Sreela, holds a BSc with Chemistry Honors from Calcutta University, followed by a BTech from Jadavpur University in Food Technology and Biochemical Engineering. About 12 years back whe took up a teaching assignment in SNDT University, Pune. She taught there for about ten years, before she decided to devote her time to social work. I am a Mechanical Engineer from REC Durgapur, with a Post-Graduate degree from the Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay. I have been working in the field of Automobile Design for over 35 years, and am currently a Senior VP at a leading Automobile company in India. We originally hail from Jessore (Bangladesh) - where my grandfather was a well-known landowner and freedom fighter. My father worked as an executive in Burmah Shell, and my mother held a double MA (Sanskrit and Bengali) from Calcutta University. She was a professor of Sanskrit. Both my parents are no more. My older brother is a senior executive at a world-leading US firm, and is settled in the US. He has a daughter who is a doctor, and two sons. One of them is a Harvard-educated lawyer while the other works in the US State Department. We are Barendra Brahmins, while my wife is a Kayastha. My wife's father was an officer in the Indian Army and is no more. He hailed from a well-known family originally from Bhagalpur. Her maternal side is originally from Bikrampur (Dhaka). column1:
I was born and brought up with mixture of traditional and modern values.
I am decent, amiable, soft-spoken person with great attitude towards life,
stable and compassionate with a pleasing personality. 
My parents though more inclined towards traditional values, understand and 
follow the modern values as a part of life.
I am well settled in mumbai with my family where I am working as lead position 
in a reputed top MNC software firm .

Being from a middle class famlily the most important thing for me in 
life is values which are strongly instilled in me.
I am fast adeptable ....I consider it helps me to embrace change...
I take much time to get mix with people....but once establish a relationship...
neither leave them nor let them leave...
I am good at convincing people.....either by words or by tears...
I give others more importance than me ...
During my leisure time I use to enjoy nature and enjoy the company of friend.

My goals in my life is to touch the sky.

I believe in concept of simple living and high thinking.

Rest I Will reveal about myself on meeting with you and your family.,"It takes hundred men to make a house but it takes one woman to build a home.
I'm thus searching for one such woman who can come into my life and make
it complete with all her love, caring and affection.
A simple, beautiful, loving, caring & amiable girl with good educational background.
A compatible person who can stand by me through thick and thin of life.
I will do best with someone who is honest, trust worthy and understanding.
She should have love for the young ones and respect for my parents and elders.","I belong to a nuclear family consisting of my parents,one sisters and myself.
My parents are very soft-spoken and liberal in nature.
My family lives at balasore, Orissa.now staying at mumbai.We are quite liberal in our values
but at the same time we follow our traditions too.
Father enjoying the retirement life and taking care ansestral propery where mother takes care of our home.Sister is younger to me and at present she has done

column1: I believe life is full of adventure, trill, fun, problems & contradictions but you have to maintain a balance. You can not get everything right but you can assess & search anything right from a wrong. No tensions just think; do it or leave it. You must be clear in your thought and everything can be contradicted or can be solved. Full happiness but a bit seriousness. There must be a bundle of hobbies and no boredom but no habit. There is no need to change life but you can change you. It is a matter of approach. Sometimes a negative approach will work. You must say 'LET IT BE'. Excess of everything is bad. But there bust be perfection in everything you do. Besides this, I enjoy going for long walks, journeys, and traveling, adventurous things or just like to try out, when i find something exciting. I tried skeying, balooning, paraglyding, river-rafting etc. I visited many places specially Jabalpur, Amarnath, Kedarnath, neelkanth etc. many times. My date of birth is 15.11.77. Place:Panipat at 11:40 P.M.,"I wish to spend my life with someone who is considerate, loving, communicative, frank with me at least, with whom I can share everything, with whom there is no need to tell a lie, romantic and fun to be with... yes, someone very special....... Whatever the circumstances a smile on whose face would mean a lot to me and vice versa :) .....this may sound like over-high expectations, but I feel that these qualities, together with mutual love, respect, commitment, honesty understanding and trust are important for an interesting &  happy marriage. Needless to say, honesty is a sine qua non of it! She will get the same response with me also. She must have a bit humour with a sought of forgiveness and forgetness of the silly things in life. She has to just look at me in the tense surroundings. Till we are right, no situation can make us puzzle. It is equally important to take it in a spirit of practicality, which doesn?t make us neglect our responsibilities and aims!!

I am looking for a normal person who is intelligent, stable and would like to embark with me on this journey called life. I preferred a house wife but if she wanted she can work but she should do it for hobby not for money or security. column1:
I am a simple and honest person who is patient in life. My patience helps me in first analyzing the entire scenario and then reacting over it. Further, I am a family oriented person and like to be near my family members.    
In my professional life, I work with full dedication and do a lot of hard work in order to attain the top position in life. Presently I am working as an Assistant Manager in Fire Pro Systems Private Limited. In future I would like to continue my profession in the same field and reach the heights of success. 
My main weakness is that I am very straight forward and prefer to speak my mind freely. I feel proud of my nature as I at least don't talk behind anyone's back and this factor makes me feel proud of myself.
My mother is a homemaker and father is a farmer by profession. I have a sister who is married and well settled in her life and a brother who is working as a Research Analyst in a Government Organization.
After completing my school education I did BE from Adhiyamaan College of Engineering. 
I have very few friends in my life and they are my real support. Further, I like to spend most of my time with them watching movies and travelling to new destinations. I love to listen to some of my favorite tracks and read books.,"The girl, with whom I will get married to, should be a simple person with a homely nature. She must be religious and should give respect to the religious values. Further, she must know how to respect the traditional and cultural values.

My life partner will enjoy the freedom to choose her career. I will have no objections if she wants to work or continue as a home maker. I assure her complete support and love from my side. She should be well qualified and must come from a decent family background.

One of my major weaknesses is that I am an emotional person and it is very difficult for me to keep things in my heart for a longer period of time. I have a very loveable and supporting family who always support me in every situation of life and also guides me the correct path that leads to success. 
My family includes my sweet mother who is a housewife. My father is no more with us and I always miss his presence. Further, I have two children, a 3 year old boy and a new born baby girl. For me my children are the greatest achievements of life and I love them the most.

column1:
Leaving oneAA?A?s own country was the toughest thing I ever had to do. The one who leaves his own country feels he is detached from a very big community. I felt the same when I left my country. I felt as if I am being detached from where I belong.
I left my country for a better future but I always missed my country. I always felt I must return but the chords outside India held me very tight to strive and create a successful future for myself. 
My higher education was completed in Canada. Presently, IAA?A?m in Telecommunications Industry designated as a Product Manager. I enjoy my work and wish to be more successful in the same field. 
As a person, I am very hard working and have a positive attitude towards life. I'm a driven individual, with focussed goals in life. I believe life is what we make of it & I look at challenges as opportunity. 

I value finer things in life and try to maintain a balance with work and play. I enjoy working out, outdoors, reading, travelling, learning music in my leisure time.  I have many friends in both India and Canada and maintain a balance of east & west cultures.,"As I mentioned above, I live abroad. Therefore, the person interested in me must keep that I mind. She should be willing to live abroad. I do not want her to panic if I ask her to shift there.
Living in Canada is not very easy so she needs to be very adjusting and must have a good knowledge about English language. If she is flexible enough she will not have any issues adapting.

I am an open-minded individual &  understand that her needs as an individual should be met. She can have all the freedom she needs and can make as many friends as she wants. I will appreciate this and will think that she is settling down well.

Other than that, a humble family background &  balanced upbringing is desired. My partnerAA?A?s family  must understand my situation and must trust me with their daughter. I donAA?A?t want them to be worried as this will make me also very uncomfortable.

I am very practical and can take care of our household and family if needed. This will not be a problem as I am good at it. She will always have my support in everything and can feel free to tell me if she requires any help. I assure her my attention.
She should be well educated as I appreciate and respect educated people. She will have me as her friend first and then a husband. This way we can become a good couple and she can feel free with me.
I vision my partner to be truly unique and someone who is goal oriented in life. A few common interests like eating healthy, fitness, music, movies etc would help but not a strict requirement.

With all these qualities, I can give her a wonderful life ahead. ",,24 to 28,30 Jul 1978,,Canada,,Athletic,Athletic,,Kayastha,,Delhi,,Whetish Medium ,Doesn't Matter,Self,BE B.Tech (Engineering),"35 yrs, 5ft 7in,

column1:
A person who has the ability to learn from otherAA?A?s lives and their experiences can live his life in the most wonderful way. He will know how to do things and if he doesnAA?A?t he can just learn it from people. I have a habit of learning and I feel good that I am like this. People also appreciate this in me.
Since the ancient times, people who were better learners were the ones who survived. I am proud of the fact and consider this habit in me as an asset. 
I am a Finance Professional and have been working for quite some time now. People in my office like my work and appreciate me for being good at it. In future, I would like to excel in the same field and I am sure I will be able to do it as I am a good learner. 
My school education was very smooth. I was a very sincere and an attentive student. After schooling I Completed B.Com, M.Com, B.Ed and MA. Currently, I am pursuing my MBA. I was also the topper in Dayal Singh College during my graduation.
My father is a retired Assistant commissioner and my mother is a homemaker. My brother is a CA and his wife is also a homemaker. I love my family and whenever I get some time off from work, I spend it with them. Apart from that, I have few friends but they all are very close to me. 
When I am free, I like to study and read things that are important. But most of all, I like to sleep.,"The girl I get married to, can either be a homemaker or can work. I have no reservations about that. This is because I am no one to choose a career for someone and she should be comfortable with whatever she does. Also, I do not judge a person by his profession. All that is important for me is her personality and nature.
She should be well qualified and educated as I value education a lot. A person who is educated stands differently in the crowd and knows how to be reasonable with things.

When two people get married to each other they not only get to live with each other but also with each otherAA?A?s families.  Therefore, the girl I get married to must be from a good family and must know how to behave and respect her elders and give love to her youngsters.

I am a very practical person and I can help my wife in keeping the household well. I am not one of those men who feel disgraced in doing so. In fact, I will feel good that I can be of any help to her. I can take care of the family too if she is not around because of some reason.
She should be very adjustable and should not take much time in adjusting and learning the culture of our house. I am sure if she is adjusting, all my family members will adore her.

I am sure she will get to live the most wonderful life if she is what I expect her to be.",,22 to 26,11 Jul 1978,,India,Bangalore,Slim,,,Padmasali,Padmasali,,,Wheatish ,,Brother,Other Post Graduation,"35 yrs, 5ft 9in,

column1: The fragrance of rain drenching the parched earth, the flash of lightning against an ink-blue sky, the temple bells chiming on festival day... itA?s these small pleasures in life that make me happy. For me, festivals related to Lord Shankar are very important A he is our family deity after all. But I respect all religions and faiths. When I am passing by a church, gurudwara or masjid, my hands immediately fold into a Namaste as a mark of reverence. For me all religions are the same and lead to almighty.
